quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  18,35,"And he entered his garden, while he was a wrong-doer in respect of his own soul; he said: I imagine not that this shall ever perish"
  18,36,"Nor I imagine that the Hour is going to happen; and if am brought back to my Lord, surely I will find something better than this as a retreat"
  18,37,"His fellow said unto him, while he spake with him: hast thou disbelieved in Him Who created thee of dust, then of a sperm, and formed thee a man"
  18,38,"But he is Allah, my Lord; and with my Lord associate not anyone"
  18,39,"Wherefore saidst thou not, when thou enteredest thy garden: whatsoever Allah may will! there is no power save in Allah! If thou beholdest I am inferior to thee in substance and offspring"
  18,40,Then belike my Lord will vouchsafe unto me something better than thy garden and send thereon a belt from the heaven that it become a plane slippery
  18,41,Or the water thereof become deep sunken so that therefor thou canst not make a search
  18,42,"And his property was encompassed; and lo! he was wringing the palms of his hands over that which he had expended thereon, while itlay fallen down on its trellises, and saying: Oh, would that had not associated with my Lord anyone"
  18,43,"And there could be no party suceouring him as against Allah, nor could he himself be an avenger"
  18,44,"Herein is all protection from Allah the True: He is excellent in respect of reward and excellent in respect of the final end"
  18,45,"And propound thou unto them the similitude of the life of the World. It is as water which We send down from the heaven, then there mingleth therewith the vegetation of the earth, and lo! it becometh dry stubble which the winds scatter and Allah is over everything potent"